The paper addresses the task of video object segmentation, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The proposed pipeline involves tracking and self-adaptation, which are related to robotics and machine learning, respectively. Therefore, it is also possible that the paper belongs to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions inter-frame consistency and real-time speed, which are related to multimedia and computer graphics, respectively. Hence, it is possible that the paper belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
